##Diary of the siege of Wuhan | Day twenty-three

Techread

Features, Lanxi, founder of zhulu.com  , focuses on in-depth observations and business reviews of Internet startups, new media, and subcultures.

It is said that Wuhan originally planned to resume full work from now on, and then temporarily issued a document to put it off until next week.

Obviously, the current situation does not meet the conditions for the resumption of work, but the toothpaste-like delay, but also revealed to the economic needs, so caught in a dilemma.

Local businesses are similarly jittery, with many urging employees to return to work, but the risk of infection and contagion from the gathering is too great to bear that they might have to foot the bill.

In this period of time, Xibei's Jia Guolong and Mei KTV's Wu Hai came out shouting, for entrepreneurs to seek a lot of attention, mainly for the loss of cash flow to reduce the burden of enterprises.

It is usually only at this point that people realize how difficult it is to run a business, every cost is a debt, can not pay will go bankrupt.

Mr. Dareka no Negai Ga Kanau Koro, who received a special bank loan, and Mr. Wu, who has a reputation for writing letters to the prime minister, are likely to get a good following, but they are not the only businesses under heavy pressure across the country.

Crying babies can't always be the only ones who get the milk.

There is also a widely held view that policies everywhere have adjusted corporate social security expenditures to late withholding rather than relief, which does not actually serve as a burden-sharing function and does not fit in well with the practice of special periods.

During the unprecedented long vacation, the relationship between the company and the employees may get better, and the employees fear that the endless work stoppage will one day bring the company to a halt and create a symbiotic feeling of being in the same trench, it eliminates the binary structure that was once seen as exploitative and exploited.

In a sense, the joke goes, the new crown pneumonia played the role of Dr. Manhattan, the architect of the coming of understanding and solidarity.

And then there's the so-called middle class, who, in the age of scarcity, expressed their frustration at having nowhere to spend their money, and in a poll on "who did you miss the most during the epidemic? " , The answer came in first in a way you probably couldn't have imagined, it's "cleaning lady" ..

It's like the bedroom and living room behind the polls, where so many people have been turned upside down by this, by pretense, by weakness, all out of a yearning for order, just like two months ago, all the things people enjoy when they wish to leave the old and welcome the new.

It's a mess, Faraway, So Close! .

I remember Peter Drucker giving an example of how to experience the Zeitgeist when, in his early 20s, he became assistant editor in chief of a prominent European daily.

"I was promoted not because I was exceptional, but because the people who were supposed to be in those positions, journalists in their 30s and 40s, were hard to find in Europe, " Peter Drucker said, most of them died on the battlefield in the first World War, so even high-ranking positions had to be filled by young men like me. "

This reminds me again, someone commented under the news item about elderly people in Wuhan dying of diseases and jumping to their deaths without help, saying that what does this mean? It means that he has experienced unimaginable hardships in his lifetime for those of us, we survived the war of resistance, the anti-rightist struggle, the cultural revolution, the famine, and then in our nineties, we couldn't stand the despair of dying.

That's what hurts.

This is my diary of the siege of Wuhan, Day twenty-three.
